title: PC3E_rep1 (MiSeq)
characteristics_ch1.3: media: DMEM/F12 with 10% FBS, 1%NEAA and 400 μg/ml G418
treatment_protocol_ch1: Plated 3M cells of each type in 10 cm diameter dishes and harvested after overnight incubation
growth_protocol_ch1: Cell lines were maintained in DMEM/F12 with 10% FBS, 1%NEAA and 400 μg/ml G418.
extract_protocol_ch1: Cells were washed with PBS 3x and then extracted with Trizol and flash frozen at -80C
extract_protocol_ch1.1: Libraries were prepared for sequencing using Illumina TruSeq Stranded Total RNA kit according to the manufacturer's instructions.
description: RASL-seq was performed solely on MiSeq
data_processing.5: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: kallisto.tar.gz: processed files for HiSeq 4000 experiments
data_processing.6: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: RASL_count.txt (MiSeq): the two comma-separated values correspond to the number of reads supporting Inclusion Isoform (first number) vs. Skipping Isoform (second number)
data_processing.7: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: darts_read_counts.txt: """"I1"""", """"S1"""" represent the number of RNA-seq reads supporting Inclusion/Skipping isoforms in PC3E cell line, where the read counts in replicate 1,2,3 are separated by comma. Similarly, """"I2"""", """"S2"""" are read counts from GS689 replicate 1,2,3.
media:ch1: DMEM/F12 with 10% FBS, 1%NEAA and 400 μg/ml G418
